The paper deals with program transformation and type systems for distributed programs, which are topics that are commonly studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the partitioning of heaps and the preservation of typing properties, which are relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a system of inference rules, which is related to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category.
